title: Cross Country: 3 Streaks earn All-Conference honors
text: Posted Oct. 15, 2015 at 9:59 PM Updated at 9:59 PM Posted Oct. 15, 2015 at 9:59 PM HAMPTON — Galesburg High School cross country runners Joe Stewart and Kaitlyn Pendergast each finished second in their respective races at the Western Big 6 Meet at Empire Park on Thursday. Stewart, Pendergast and Anastasia Beetler each earned All-Conference with their top seven finishes. Stewart finished the three mile boys race in 15:54. Kyle Riege (United Township) won with a time of 15:44.0. Galesburg’s Bricyn Healey took 12th in 16:50 and Wilson Burton was 14th in 17:00.0. Jakob Pettit took 27th in 17:50.5 and Aaron Burrows finished out the Silver Streaks’ scoring with a 30th-place time of 18:04.0. Galesburg finished in fourth-place with an 82. Alleman won the meet with 45 points and United Township was second with 45. Pendergast had a time of 19:28.0 and Rock Island’s Agok Ayuen time of 19:04 was good enough for first place. Beetler crossed the line in fifth in 20:04.0. Lexi Herr took 15th in 20:35.0, Jordan Shroyer was 31st in 21:49 and Anna Robinson finished in 32nd in 21:56 for GHS. The Streaks took fifth with an 85. Rock Island took the top spot with a 61 and Alleman was second with 68. The Register-Mail
